ability of an enduring genre, studying iconic films along the way.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aRoad filmsxHistory and criticism. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh1 aArcher, Neil, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertColumbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311063857840uhttps://doi.org/10.7312/arch1764740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780231850889423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780231850889/original  a978-3-11-063857-8  Columbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles